JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma has rejected another Sunday Times report.
	
	The paper has published an extract of a book by investigative journalist Jacques Pauw. In the book, Pauw claims Zuma is a serial tax evader. READ:Â Jacob Zuma survives motion of no confidence He alleges the president owed around R63-million in tax on fringe benefits related to his Nkandla home. Pauw also claims Zuma was employed by a company, founded by his friend and ANC supporter, Roy Moodley. Pauw says Zuma was paid a million rand a month, but didn't declare it to Sars. The Presidency insists Zuma's tax affairs are in order. It says the reports are misleading and part of a smear campaign. eNCA